full_text: Study finds that 37% of ACOs reported having a non-provider management partner. In these ACOs, the partner frequently provided essential services for success such as: data services (94%), administrative (87%), education (67%) care coordination (65%).https://t.co/d967agwYL3
From @Health_Affairs: The Hidden Roles That Management Partners Play In Accountable Care Organizations https://t.co/rGjxVkAJUB
New @DartmouthInst #study in @Health_Affairs explores how #ACOs work with different types of #management partners: https://t.co/1mPD3CDUrZ
